x4freetext: The neutron source was a 1/2" thick Be target.
The neutrons were detected by measuring the
activity induced in carbon disks according to the
Of the solids, C, Al, Cu, Sn and Pb were machined to
the standard 2.5" diameter. U and Be to 2" diameter.
Mg and Zn blocks of 3 and 2" squares, respectively.
Paraffin was used for H cross section using paraffin-
carbon difference. Li was in 2x2x1" rough blocks.
Liquids were in 2.5" diameter thin-aluminum wall cell.
Only powdered substance melamine (C3H6N6), from which N
cross section was extracted, was in 2.5" Al tube.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: The errors given with the final results
are the mean statistical errors, plus 1% added to
allow for other unspecified sources of error.
The error arising from scattering of neutrons into
the detector by the heavier elements are not quite
negligible, on account of small angular spread of the
diffraction patterns at this neutron energy.
Therefore, corrections were made for this effect.
